reece.net Greek SuperLeague official Site]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070613222837/http://www.galanissportsdata.com/sdatesgr.asp SuperLeague Statistics]\n\n{{Super League Greece seasons}}\n{{1964\u201365 in Greek football}}\n{{1964\u201365 in European Football (UEFA)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1964-65 Alpha Ethniki}}\n[[Category:Alpha Ethniki seasons]]\n[[Category:1964\u201365 in European association football leagues|Greece]]\n[[Category:1964\u201365 in Greek football]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[Alpha Ethniki]]\n| season             = 1964\u201365\n| winners            = [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]<br/>8th Greek title\n| relegated          = [[Apollon Pontou FC|Apollon Kalamarias]]<br/>[[Doxa Drama F.C.|Doxa Drama]]\n| continentalcup1    = [[1965-66 European Cup|European Cup]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]\n| continentalcup2    = [[1965-66 European Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n| continentalcup3    = [[1965-66 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup|Inter-Cities Fairs Cup]]\n| continentalcup3 qualifiers = [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]<br/>[[PAOK FC|PAOK]]\n| league topscorer   = [[Giorgos Sideris]] (24)\n| biggest home win   = \n| biggest away win   = \n| highest scoring    = \n| matches            = 240\n| total goals        = 674\n| longest wins       = \n| longest unbeaten   = \n| longest winless    = \n| longest losses     = \n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance  = \n| prevseason         = [[1963\u201364 Alpha Ethniki|1963\u201364]]\n| nextseason         = [[1965\u201366 Alpha Ethniki|1965\u201366]]\n}}\n\n'''[[Super League Greece|Alpha Ethniki]]''' 1964-65 complete season\n\n{{Location map+ |Greece |width=380 |float=right|caption=Location of teams in '''1964\u201365 Alpha Ethniki''' |places=\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=37.966667 |long=23.716667 |label=<small>[[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]</small><br><